    "comment": "Rationale: PSDs were isolated from the forebrains of 30 days old untreated rats and analysed by mass spectrometry.\n\n\"Poly(rC)-binding protein 1\" is listed in table 1 as NCBI protein gi|6754994\n\nfrom https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/6754994 this maps to MGI:1345635 = uniprot identifier P60335. This is a mouse protein, so it appears the original publication used a multi-species database (which was not uncommon at time of publication). The matching identifier in rat genome database is RGD:1561319 and NCBI gene ID 500242.. Experimental description: 30-days-old rats; subspecies not specified.",
